WITH PATIENCE running thin amid rampant inflation and a devaluing currency, trade unions in Argentina have organised two days of strikes against the government of Mauricio Macri. Taiwan’s richest man has announced his bid to become the country's president. But with much of his business based in China, he will struggle to convince voters that he has no conflicts of interest. And America’s Supreme Court is deciding whether to ensure trademark protection for businesses with vulgar names. Runtime: 20 min.    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn